    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Add your<strong> bulgur wheat </strong>to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> (the same as you would for pasta) and cook over a high heat for an initial 4 min</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/salmon-with-courgette-ribbon-and-greek-cheese-salad/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the bulgur wheat is cooking, heat a large, dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>flaked almonds </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until toasted and golden</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don't burn!</p><p>Once golden, transfer to a plate</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/salmon-with-courgette-ribbon-and-greek-cheese-salad/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the pan to a medium-high heat with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>salmon fillet[s]</strong>, skin-side down</p><p>Cook for 9-10 min, turning once halfway, until golden and cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/salmon-with-courgette-ribbon-and-greek-cheese-salad/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the bulgur wheat has had an initial 4 min,\u00a0add your<strong> blanched peas</strong> to\u00a0the pot<strong> </strong>and cook for a further 5-6 min or until the bulgur wheat is cooked and tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain everything and return to the pot</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/salmon-with-courgette-ribbon-and-greek-cheese-salad/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel your <strong>courgette[s]</strong> with a peeler until you end up with a pile of courgette ribbons</p><p>Crumble your <strong>Greek cheese </strong>into rough bite-sized pieces</p><p>Strip your <strong>mint leaves</strong> from their stems and chop them\u00a0finely, discard the stems</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/salmon-with-courgette-ribbon-and-greek-cheese-salad/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the juice of<strong> half</strong> your <strong>lemon[s]</strong> to a bowl with 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>water</strong></p><p>Add a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and stir it all together\u00a0\u2013 this is your <strong>lemon dressing</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining lemon</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p><p>Wash your<strong> salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/salmon-with-courgette-ribbon-and-greek-cheese-salad/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the\u00a0<strong>courgette ribbons</strong>,<strong> salad</strong>, <strong>crumbled Greek cheese</strong>, most of the<strong> chopped mint </strong>(save the rest for garnish!)<strong> </strong>and <strong>lemon dressing</strong>\u00a0to the cooked\u00a0bulgur wheat</p><p>Give everything a gentle mix up \u2013 this is your<strong> courgette ribbon & Greek cheese salad</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/salmon-with-courgette-ribbon-and-greek-cheese-salad/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>courgette ribbon & Greek cheese salad</strong> with the<strong> salmon</strong> to the side</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>toasted</strong> <strong>flaked almonds</strong>,\u00a0<strong>remaining chopped mint</strong> and a <strong>lemon wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
